Package: ggwidth
Title: Standardise 'ggplot2' Width
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("David", "Hodge", , "davidhodge931@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3868-7501"))
Description: The objective of 'ggwidth' is to standardise the appearance of
    widths in 'ggplot2' geoms such as 'geom_bar()', 'geom_col()',
    'geom_boxplot()', 'geom_errorbar()', and
    'ggbeeswarm::geom_quasirandom()'. It ensures these geoms appear visually
    consistent across plots with different numbers of categories, panel
    dimensions, and orientations.
